White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki provided an update on several topics during a press briefing. She discussed the progress made in addressing the Colonial Pipeline supply disruptions, the decrease in unemployment insurance claims, and the launch of the Veteran Rapid Retraining Assistance Program. Psaki also mentioned the Senate Judiciary Committee's vote on the nomination of Kristen Clarke to be Assistant Attorney General for Civil Rights. She addressed questions about President Biden's meeting with President Putin, the violence in Israel, and the payment of ransom by Colonial Pipeline. Psaki also mentioned the possibility of changes to the legislation for granting statehood to the District of Columbia and the need for infrastructure investment.